title: int
description: An integer value, up to 64 bits.

title: double
description: A double precision floating point value, up to 64 bits.

title: string
description: A character string.

title: boolean
description: A true/false value.

title: collection
description: A playlist or collection of songs

title: song
description: A provider-agnostic piece of music that can be interacted with through service providers.

title: album
description: A provider-agnostic musical album that can be interacted with through service providers.

title: list
description: A dynamic collection of types.

title: java
description: A reference to a Java object, for interacting with native methods.

title: function
description: A Qilletni native type.

title: Artist
description: An artist who creates songs.

title: Artist(_id, _name)
description: Creates a new artist with the given ID and name. The id is a string that is identifiable by the provider which owns this artist. An example of this is a standard Spotify ID.

title: fun getId()
description: Gets the ID of the artist.

title: fun getName()
description: Gets the name of the artist.

title: Date
description: An entity that may store a date (not time).

title: Date(_date)
description: Creates a new date with the given date .

title: native static fun parse(str)
description: Creates a new date from a DD/MM/YYYY formatted string.

title: native static fun now()
description: Gets a new date from the current time.

title: native fun getDay()
description: Gives the day of the month, as a number starting at 1.

title: native fun getDayName()
description: Gets the name of the day.

title: native fun getMonth()
description: Gives the month of the year, as a number between 1-12.

title: native fun getMonthName()
description: Gets the name of the month.

title: native fun getYear()
description: Gives the year.

title: Map
description: A HashMap wrapper that may store keys and values of any type.

title: static fun fromList(list)
description: Creates a new map from a list of key-value pairs.

title: native fun put(key, value)
description: Puts a key and value into the map, overriding any previous value associated with the key.

title: native fun get(key)
description: Gets a value from the map by its key .

title: native fun containsKey(key)
description: Checks if the map contains the key key .

title: native fun containsValue(value)
description: Checks if the map contains any entry with the value value .

title: native fun keys()
description: Gets a list of all keys in the map.

title: native fun values()
description: Gets a list of all values in the map.

title: Optional
description: An entity that may either hold a value or be empty. The value being held may be anything.

title: Optional(_value, _hasValue)
description: Creates a new optional with the given value and if it has a value. It is strongly recommended to just use fromValue() or fromEmpty()

title: static fun fromValue(value)
description: Creates an optional from a value.

title: static fun fromEmpty()
description: Creates an empty optional.

title: fun hasValue()
description: Checks if the optional has a value.

title: fun getValue()
description: Gets the value of the optional. This will stop the program if the optional is empty, so check first via hasValue().

title: fun clearValue()
description: Clears the value of the optional.

title: fun setValue(value)
description: Sets the value of the optional.

title: static fun fromList(list)
description: Creates a new queue from a list of elements.

title: fun enqueue(element)
description: Enqueues an element onto the queue.

title: fun dequeue()
description: Dequeues an element from the queue.

title: fun peek()
description: Peeks at the front element of the queue.

title: fun isEmpty()
description: Checks if the queue is empty.

title: fun size()
description: Gets the size of the queue.

title: fun toList()
description: Converts the queue to a list.

title: static fun fromList(list)
description: Creates a new stack from a list of elements.

title: fun push(element)
description: Pushes an element onto the stack.

title: fun pop()
description: Pops an element from the stack.

title: fun peek()
description: Peeks at the top element of the stack.

title: fun isEmpty()
description: Checks if the stack is empty.

title: fun size()
description: Gets the size of the stack.

title: fun toList()
description: Converts the stack to a list.

title: User
description: An end user/listener of a song provider that may own playlists.

title: User(_id, _name)
description: Creates a new user with the given ID and name. The id is a string that is identifiable by the provider which owns this user. An example of this is a standard Spotify ID.

title: fun getId()
description: Gets the ID of the user.

title: fun getName()
description: Gets the name of the user.

title: native fun getAllArtists() on album
description: Gets all Artist s of the album.

title: native fun getArtist() on album
description: Gets the primary Artist of the album.

title: native fun getId() on album
description: Gets the ID of an album.

title: native fun getName() on album
description: Gets the name of an album.

title: native fun getUrl() on album
description: Gets the URL of an album.

title: native fun anySongMatches(fn) on collection
description: Loops through all songs of the collection and checks if the condition is matched.

title: native fun containsArtist(artist) on collection
description: Checks if the collection contains any song with the given artist as the song's first artist.

title: native fun getCreator() on collection
description: Gets the creator of the collection.

title: native fun getId() on collection
description: Gets the ID of the collection. This is an ID identifiable by the provider which owns this collection.

title: native fun getName() on collection
description: Gets the name of the collection.

title: native fun getTrackCount() on collection
description: Gets the number of tracks in the collection.

title: native fun getUrl() on collection
description: Gets the URL of the collection.

title: native fun nextSong() on collection
description: Gets the next song as if it were being played.

title: native fun add(item) on list
description: Adds an item to the list.

title: native fun add(index, item) on list
description: Adds an item to the list at the specified index.

title: native fun addAll(itemList) on list
description: Adds all items of the given list to the current list.

title: native fun contains(item) on list
description: Checks if the given item is contained in the list.

title: native fun indexOf(item) on list
description: Checks the index of the given item in the list.

title: fun isEmpty(lst) on list
description: Checks if the list is empty.

title: native fun join(delimiter) on list
description: Joins the items of the list into a single string.

title: native fun remove(index) on list
description: Removes an item from the list at the given index.

title: native fun size() on list
description: Gets the size of the list.

title: native fun sort() on list
description: Sorts a list of numbers or strings in-place.

title: native fun sortReverse() on list
description: Sorts a list of numbers or strings in-place, in reverse order.

title: native fun subList(fromIndex, toIndex) on list
description: Returns a portion of the current list from the specified starting index to the end of the list.

title: native fun getAlbum() on song
description: Gets the Album the song is on.

title: native fun getAllArtists() on song
description: Gets all Artist entities on the song.

title: native fun getArtist() on song
description: Gets the Artist entity of the primary artist on the song

title: native fun getDuration() on song
description: Gets the duration of the song in milliseconds.

title: native fun getId() on song
description: Gets the ID of the song. This is an ID identifiable by the provider which owns this song.

title: native fun getTitle() on song
description: Gets the name of the song.

title: native fun getUrl() on song
description: Gets the URL of the song. If it was not defined with a URL, an empty string is returned.

title: native fun contains(comparing) on string
description: Checks if the string contains the given string.

title: native fun format(formatList) on string
description: Performs typical C-style string formatting. Only strings, doubles, and integers are supported.

title: native fun length() on string
description: Gets the length of a string.

title: native fun substring(beginIndex) on string
description: Returns a substring of the current string from the given index.

title: native fun substring(beginIndex, endIndex) on string
description: Returns a substring of the current string from and to specified indices

title: native fun toInt() on string
description: Converts the string to an integer.

title: native fun toLower() on string
description: Returns the string in all lowercase.

title: native fun toUpper() on string
description: Returns the string in all uppercase.

title: native fun _emptyJavaMap()
description: Creates an empty HashMap instance.

title: native fun backtrace()
description: Prints out the current stacktrace of the program.

title: native fun breakpoint()
description: Pauses the program and puts the user in a debugger.

title: native fun breakpoint(condition)
description: Pauses the program and puts the user in a debugger if the given condition is true.

title: native fun bt()
description: Prints out the current stacktrace of the program.

title: native fun currentTimeMillis()
description: Gets the current time in milliseconds

title: native fun defaultPlay(songToPlay)
description: Play a song via the default "play" keyword invoked as a function, which will call the default "play" action as if no redirection happened.

title: native fun exit(code)
description: Exits the program with the given exit code.

title: native fun functions()
description: Prints out the functions in the current scope and all parents.

title: native fun functions(entityInstance)
description: Prints out the functions in the given entity's scope and all parents.

title: native fun getEnv(name)
description: Gets the environment variable of a given name. This will return a string, or throw an error if it can't be found.

title: fun getEnv(name, default)
description: Gets the environment variable of a given name. If the value is not found, a default value is returned.

title: native fun hasEnv(name)
description: Checks if an environment variable is set.

title: native fun print(obj)
description: Prints a string representation of the given object to the console, followed by a newline character.

title: fun printf(obj, formatParams)
description: Prints a given string to the console, followed by a newline character. The string is formatted with string.format using the parameters provided.

title: native fun processBackground()
description: Process background tasks until the program is terminated.

title: native fun random(min, max)
description: Generates a random integer between an inclusive lower bound and an exclusive upper bound.

title: native fun readLine()
description: Reads a line of input from the console.

title: native fun redirectPlayToFunction(fn)
description: Starts making all plays invoke the given function with 1 parameter of the song.

title: native fun redirectPlayToList(songList)
description: Starts making all plays add to a song list instead of the previous play action.

title: native fun redirectReset()
description: Stops all 'play's from any set action and returns it back to its default action.

description: Sets the resolve strategy of fetched tracks to the given strategy. The strategy is

title: native fun vars()
description: Prints out the variables and their values in the current scope and all parents.

title: native fun vars(entityInstance)
description: Prints out the variables and their values in the given entity's scope and all parents.
